            <fr:title text="More examples and handy forms">More examples and handy forms</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let's look at some more example axiomatic proofs in these systems.
In the course of this, I'll introduce three more forms: <html:strong>B</html:strong>, <html:strong>C</html:strong>, and <html:strong>W</html:strong>.
We won't use these forms to add any additional axioms, or to develop any new proof systems.
Rather, we'll use them to think a bit about what we can <html:em>already</html:em> show in the systems we have.
(Also, remember that you don't need to memorise these forms, or anything else for that matter!
You can always come back to these lectures whenever you need to.)</html:p>
